29/06/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Four countries -- Bulgaria, Croatia, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro -- are marking the Day of the Danube River on Wednesday (29 June). 
The four, along with nine other states in Europe, are signatories to the 1994 international convention for the protection of the Danube. 
(BNR, HRT, Rompres - 29/06/05)
